# Project Structure (Generic Template)

## Directory Layout

```
{root}/
├── src/
│   ├── apps/{app-name}/              ← Deployable FE/mobile apps (NX projects)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   ├── docs/                     ← architecture/, adr/, features/{feature-id}/
│   │   └── project.json
│   ├── services/{service-name}/      ← Backend services (NX projects)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   ├── db/migrations/            ← Service-local SQL migrations (if applicable)
│   │   ├── docs/                     ← architecture/, adr/, features/{feature-id}/
│   │   ├── Dockerfile
│   │   └── project.json
│   └── shared/
│       ├── libs/{name}/              ← Shared libraries (ui, types, utils, config...)
│       └── assets/                   ← Shared static assets
├── infra/                            ← Docker, K8s, Terraform, CI configs
├── tools/generators/                 ← NX custom generators
├── docs/                             ← Cross-cutting docs only
│   ├── architecture/                 ← system-context, containers, tech-radar, adr/
│   ├── business/                     ← vision, domain-model, stakeholders
│   └── data/                         ← Master data, schemas
├── docker-compose.yml
├── AGENTS.md
└── nx.json, package.json, tsconfig.base.json
```

## File Placement Patterns

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| Workspace config (nx.json, tsconfig.base.json) | Root only |
| Workspace ADR (affects ≥2 projects) | `docs/architecture/adr/` |
| Project ADR (one project only) | `{project_path}/docs/adr/` |
| Feature pipeline artifacts | `{project_path}/docs/features/{feature-id}/` |
| Cross-cutting feature (PM designates) | `docs/features/{feature-id}` |
| Shared components (≥2 apps) | `src/shared/libs/ui/src/` |
| Service Dockerfile | Collocated: `{project_path}/Dockerfile` |

## Docs Path Formula

```
project-path = src/apps/{name}  OR  src/services/{name}
docs-path    = {project-path}/docs/features/{feature-id}
adr-path     = {project-path}/docs/adr/
```

Feature locate: `docs/feature-map.yaml` → lookup `features.{id}.docs_path` (PRIMARY, avoids glob).

## NX Project Tags Convention

Every `project.json` should include:
```json
{
  "tags": [
    "scope:{project-name}",
    "type:{app|service|lib}",
    "platform:{web|mobile|node|dotnet|python|java|rust|...}",
    "ui-template:{template-name|none}"
  ]
}
```

Agents use NX MCP `get_project_details({name})` to read tags — no manual lookup needed.
